### Feature request
After using schematics for the first time recently I was trying to move one (or a few files) from one directory to another and found it to be incredibly difficult. It would be nice to be able to create a tree from a [glob pattern](https://docs.python.org/2/library/glob.html) url.

My use case was moving a `package.json` file from one directory to another by using a schematics "factory".

```ts
export function movePackage( _options: Options ): Rule {
  return ( _host: Tree, _context: SchematicContext ) => {
    return mergeWith( apply( url( 'path/to/app/root' ), [
      filter( ( path: Path ) => {
        // This will visit and check EVERY file in the directory
        return path === '/package.json';
      } ),
      move( '.', 'some/destination/path' ),
    ] ) );
  };
}
```

```ts
export function movePackage( _options: Options ): Rule {
  return ( _host: Tree, _context: SchematicContext ) => {
    return mergeWith( apply( url( 'path/to/app/root/*.json' ), [
      filter( ( path: Path ) => {
        // This will visit only .json files in the top level of the directory
        return path === '/package.json';
      } ),
      move( '.', 'some/destination/path' ),
    ] ) );
  };
}
```

The difference is that you are able to pass the `url` function a glob path to build a tree only based on the files that match that pattern. Then I could filter on a subset of files, rather than having schematics look through every file, including `node_modules` just to move the file(s) I want.
```diff
export function movePackage( _options: Options ): Rule {
  return ( _host: Tree, _context: SchematicContext ) => {
-    return mergeWith( apply( url( 'path/to/app/root' ), [
+    return mergeWith( apply( url( 'path/to/app/root/*.json' ), [
      filter( ( path: Path ) =>  path === '/package.json' ),
      move( '.', 'some/destination/path' ),
    ] ) );
  };
}
```

Currently, the `url` function calls the `createSourceFromUrl` method which ignores any glob path and creates a new null host tree. `createSourceFromUrl` could be refactored to return a tree of files only for a given glob path.

https://github.com/angular/angular-cli/blob/c5de8e3b0e5c1499a0a17da0208297cd82b36095/packages/angular_devkit/schematics/src/rules/url.ts#L12-L16

https://github.com/angular/angular-cli/blob/c5de8e3b0e5c1499a0a17da0208297cd82b36095/packages/angular_devkit/schematics/tools/file-system-engine-host-base.ts#L269-L283

> Through my research of this implementation I was unable to find any other way of achieving this. If someone has an idea other than this implementation that is currently supported, I would love to be enlightened. Thanks üëç

